title: Fernhill G4/G5 — media and channel beats degrade legibly in text
story: fernhill
description: The browser-presentation layer (ambient wind, boiler thump,
  folly photograph, clock channel) is gated on `client has` flags that all
  read FALSE in the text client. Every media beat's turn must show its
  prose degradation and never leak an asset name, event key, or payload
  into the transcript.
---

# --- Grounds ambient (play ambient night-wind, gated on sound): the
# crossing reactions still speak their prose lines and nothing leaks ---
> north
[OK: contains "Gravel Drive"]

> north
[OK: contains "Fountain Court"]

# Crossing Grounds -> House: `stop ambient` sits before out-of-the-wind
> north
[OK: contains "out of the wind"]
[OK: contains "old hush"]
[OK: not contains "night-wind"]
[OK: not contains "media."]

# --- G4 image (show image folly-photograph on examining): in text the
# description IS the degradation; the asset name never leaks ---
> examine the photograph
[OK: contains "squinting into some summer"]
[OK: not contains "folly-photograph"]
[OK: not contains "images/"]

# --- G5 clock channel: wind the clock, then catch a chime. The emit
# (estate-clock with hour ...) is channel-only — text clients hear the
# chime prose and never see the event key or payload ---
> take the grey overcoat
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> search the overcoat
[OK: contains "winding key"]

> take the winding key
[OK: contains "take the winding key from"]

> wind the clock
[OK: contains "begins to walk again"]

[DO]
> wait
[OK: contains_any "Time passes" "counts the quarter"]
[UNTIL "counts the quarter"]

> wait
[OK: not contains "estate-clock"]
[OK: not contains "hour"]

# --- Re-entering the Grounds (play ambient again, gated): the cold line
# still speaks ---
> south
[OK: contains_any "The cold finds you" "The cold again"]
[OK: not contains "audio/"]

# --- G4 sound (play sound boiler-thump when the machine lights): the
# on-enter prose is the degradation ---
> east
[OK: contains "old coal dust"]

> turn the stopcock
[OK: contains "water gurgles"]

> push the primer
[OK: contains "thumps home"]

> turn on the boiler
[OK: contains "warmth crawls toward the greenhouse"]
[OK: not contains "boiler-thump"]
[OK: not contains "media."]

# The win-ending music cue (play music dawn-theme, gated on music) is
# exercised by the wt-01 walkthrough chain reaching the win with no leak.
